The paper focuses on the security of serverless computing, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the implementation of their approach on top of specific serverless platforms, which falls under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of static and dynamic labeling, which falls under the category of programming languages (cs.PL) and software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper presents case studies demonstrating the effectiveness of their approach, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
